<section xml:id="C4.S42">
<title>Solution of Triangles</title>           
<subsection xml:id="C4.S42.SS1">
<title>Planar Right Triangles</title>                     
               
<sentence sentence-num-in-section="1" xml:id="C4.S42.F1.s1">
Figure 4.42.1: Planar right triangle.
</sentence>  
<para xml:id="C4.S42.SS1.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="2" xml:id="C4.S42.SS1.p1.s1">
 <Math equation-number="4.42.1" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S42.E1">\sin A=\frac{a}{c}=\frac{1}{\csc A},</Math> <Math equation-number="4.42.2" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S42.E2">\cos A=\frac{b}{c}=\frac{1}{\sec A},</Math> <Math equation-number="4.42.3" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S42.E3">\tan A=\frac{a}{b}=\frac{1}{\cot A}</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>

 
</subsection>
 
<subsection xml:id="C4.S42.SS2">
<title>Planar Triangles</title>                                    
<sentence sentence-num-in-section="3" xml:id="C4.S42.F2.s1">
Figure 4.42.2: Planar triangle.
</sentence>  
<para xml:id="C4.S42.SS2.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="4" xml:id="C4.S42.SS2.p1.s1">
 <Math equation-number="4.42.4" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S42.E4">\frac{a}{\sin A}=\frac{b}{\sin B}=\frac{c}{\sin C},</Math> <Math equation-number="4.42.5" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S42.E5">c^{2}=a^{2}+b^{2}-2ab\cos C,</Math> <Math equation-number="4.42.6" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S42.E6">a=b\cos C+c\cos B</Math> <Math equation-number="4.42.7" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S42.E7">\hbox{area}=\tfrac{1}{2}bc\sin A=\left(s(s-a)(s-b)(s-c)\right)^{1/2},</Math> where <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C4.S42.SS2.p1.m1">s=\tfrac{1}{2}(a+b+c)</Math> (the semiperimeter).
</sentence>

</para>
 
</subsection>
 
<subsection xml:id="C4.S42.SS3">
<title>Spherical Triangles</title>                   
                  
<sentence sentence-num-in-section="5" xml:id="C4.S42.F3.s1">
Figure 4.42.3: Spherical triangle.
</sentence>  
<para xml:id="C4.S42.SS3.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="6" xml:id="C4.S42.SS3.p1.s1">
 <Math equation-number="4.42.8" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S42.E8">\cos a=\cos b\cos c+\sin b\sin c\cos A,</Math> <Math equation-number="4.42.9" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S42.E9">\frac{\sin A}{\sin a}=\frac{\sin B}{\sin b}=\frac{\sin C}{\sin c},</Math> <Math equation-number="4.42.10" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S42.E10">\sin a\cos B=\cos b\sin c-\sin b\cos c\cos A,</Math> <Math equation-number="4.42.11" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S42.E11">\cos a\cos C=\sin a\cot b-\sin C\cot B,</Math> <Math equation-number="4.42.12" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S42.E12">\cos A=-\cos B\cos C+\sin B\sin C\cos a</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
<para xml:id="C4.S42.SS3.p2">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="7" xml:id="C4.S42.SS3.p2.s1">
For these and other formulas seeSmart (1962, Chapter 1).
</sentence>

</para>
 
</subsection>
 
</section>
